 m their completed projects. Sruthi Illangovan presents “Symptom Burden\, C
 SF Opening Pressure and OCT RNFL Thickness in Pediatric Intracranial Hyper
 tension.” Illangovan is a clinical research associate with the Outcomes in
  Pediatric Neurosciences team in the UT Health Austin Pediatric Neuroscien
 ces Program at Dell Children’s Medical Center. Kevin Lanza \, Ph.D.\, pres
 ents “Can Heat Acclimatization Support Children’s Physical Activity in Sum
 mer Heat? A Feasibility Randomized Study in Austin\, Texas.” Lanza is an a
 ssistant professor in the departments of Environmental and Occupational
He
 alth Sciences and Epidemiology at UTHealth Houston School of Public Health
 . Lunch is provided to the first 35 in-person attendees. Email Shu-Ching T
 seng for the link to join virtually.\\n\\nEvent page: https://dellmed.utex
 as.edu/events/pediatric-research-seminar-pediatric-research-award-presenta
